## What I Am Still Thinking About

I feel reasonably clear on what each of the three pillars means individually. What I am less clear on is how they actually interact inside a real organization day to day.

Like — is there a dedicated GRC team? Or is governance owned by leadership, risk owned by security, and compliance owned by legal, with everyone only loosely coordinating? Who has the final say when there is a conflict between what is compliant and what is practical?

I do not have clean answers to those questions yet. But I think asking them is the right starting point. I expect this will become clearer as I get deeper into the project.

