## Why This Project, Why OpenMRS, Why AWS

I want to briefly explain the setup for anyone reading this from the beginning.

**OpenMRS** is a real, widely-used open-source EHR platform deployed in healthcare settings around the world — particularly in low-resource environments. It handles sensitive patient data, which makes it a genuinely meaningful system to practice GRC on. This is not a made-up scenario.

**AWS** is where the system is hosted in this project. Cloud environments introduce their own unique governance, risk, and compliance challenges — shared responsibility models, misconfigured services, access control — and AWS is the dominant cloud platform in real-world healthcare deployments.

Working with both means the skills I build here are directly transferable to real roles. That matters to me.

